name: Pangolin
summary: Several news articles highlight efforts to combat wildlife crime, particularly the protection of pangolins, an endangered species facing threats from illegal poaching and trafficking. Animal Survival International promotes the care of a pangolin pup, while Born Free Foundation emphasizes the need to address wildlife crime in Malawi. Live Design introduces innovative laser technology used to monitor pangolins on Lost Lands 2024. Canada's National Observer reports on trained rats detecting rhino horn and pangolin scales. China Daily shares rare images of a captured Chinese pangolin. The Forbes article mentions pangolins in a crossword puzzle. Multiple articles in India detail the seizure of pangolin scales in Darjeeling and the rescue of a pangolin in Hyderabad, leading to arrests of animal smugglers. Lastly, IOL reports on a failed attempt to sell a pangolin to Hawks, resulting in the forfeiture of a Mercedes-Benz vehicle.

name: Booker Prize 2024
summary: The 2024 Booker Prize has been awarded to British author Samantha Harvey for her novel "Orbital." The prize, which is open to English-language works of fiction from around the world, was announced in a ceremony held at London's Roundhouse on Monday, March 13th. Harvey's novel, which explores themes of space travel, human connection, and environmentalism, has been praised by critics for its lyrical prose and thought-provoking insights. The Booker Prize is one of the most prestigious literary awards in the world, and Harvey's victory is a major achievement for her career.

name: Celtic vs Chelsea
summary: In the UEFA Women's Champions League, Celtic hosted Chelsea at Celtic Park. Celtic took an early lead, but Chelsea fought back to secure a 2-1 victory. The match was closely contested, with both teams creating chances, but Chelsea's more relentless effort ultimately prevailed. The result preserved Chelsea's perfect start to the competition, while Celtic remained winless. The match was broadcast live on BBC and Eurosport and attracted a significant audience, with all eyes on Celtic's star player, Guro Reiten. The victory cemented Chelsea's position as favorites to advance from the group stage, while Celtic's hopes of progressing became more challenging.

name: Canary
summary: Canary Wharf's annual Winter Lights festival will be back this January. Health officials have issued urgent warnings for tourists traveling to the Canary Islands this winter, as several outbreaks have been reported. The Canary Islands are considering reimplementing mandatory face masks for UK tourists. The Canary Islands are currently on 'pre-alert' due to extreme weather warnings. Canary Wharf is getting a new 46-story, 912-bedroom student tower. Environmental activists from Fossil Free London protested against the Rosebank oil project. Canary Wharf is undergoing extensive developments and is now considered a highly desirable area.
